metadata.description: In 2018, 44 percent of homebuyers began their search online. Additionally, 22 percent began searching in newspaper ads and 8 percent used friend’s referrals. There is still more room for online searches to grow as tech-sophisticated Millenials and Gen Z increasingly becomes prospective home buyers.

node.title: Real Estate in a Digital Age 2020
